</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC0FE4DFFB2FFDE46E0FE44FD4657A5" blockId="2.[166,1225,447,602]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
D i s t r i b u t i o n: Palaearctic (most parts of Europe) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEE83BCFFB2FFDE45B2FE44FBD95786" author="Woodley, N. E." box="[905,1096,447,474]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" pagination="1 - 475" refId="ref4031" refString="Woodley, N. E. 2001. A world catalog of the Stratiomyidae (Insecta: Diptera). Myia, 11, 8. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, 1 - 475." type="book chapter" year="2001">Woodley, 2001</bibRefCitation>
; Popescu- Mirceni and Parvu, 2009), 
<emphasis id="B90B225FFFB2FFDE47DBFE24FD4657A5" bold="true" box="[480,727,479,505]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
first record for 
<collectingCountry id="F368BEDDFFB2FFDE44A0FE24FD4257A5" box="[667,723,479,505]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC0FE4DFFB2FFDF46E0FE04FEEC5756" blockId="2.[166,1225,447,602]" lastBlockId="3.[174,1232,175,266]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="404" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
R e m a r k: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEE83BCFFB2FFDE475CFE04FDC35446" author="Mason, F &amp; Rozkosny, R. &amp; Hauser, M." box="[359,594,511,538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" pagination="507 - 530" refId="ref3602" refString="Mason, F, Rozkosny, R., Hauser, M. 2009. A review of the soldier FLies (Diptera: Stratiomyidae) of Sardinia. Zootaxa, 2318, 507 - 530." type="journal article" year="2009">Mason et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F85CEFFB2FFDE4539FDFBFC595445" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1846" box="[770,968,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Nemotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachystomus">
<emphasis id="B90B225FFFB2FFDE4539FDFBFC595445" box="[770,968,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">N. brachystomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F85CEFFB2FFDE422BFDFBFB1C5445" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1842" box="[1040,1165,512,537]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Nemotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis id="B90B225FFFB2FFDE422BFDFBFB1C5445" box="[1040,1165,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">N. notatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species was reported under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F85CEFFB2FFDE4445FDDBFCD45465" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1846" box="[638,837,543,569]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Nemotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachystomus">
<emphasis id="B90B225FFFB2FFDE4445FDDBFCD45465" box="[638,837,543,569]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">N. brachystomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all over the Middle East. Studied specimens of this species have some variation in genitalia compared with other European and western populations, such as very long pointy inner processes. There might be several distinct species under the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7F85CEFFB3FFDF44DBFF2BFCCB56B5" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1842" box="[736,858,208,233]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Nemotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis id="B90B225FFFB3FFDF44DBFF2BFCCB56B5" box="[736,858,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">N. notatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this is beyond the scope of our investigation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
